OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAldi raises pay as         
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsupermarkets battle for    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fstaff                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Aldi has given its store employees the 
OL,6, third pay rise in 12 months, joining   
OL,7, other companies who have boosted wages 
OL,8, because of a labour shortage.          
OL,10,FThe supermarket group will lift        
OL,11,Fstarting pay to #11.40 an hour         
OL,12,Fnationally and to #12.85 in Greater    
OL,13,FLondon.                                
OL,15,FDepending on length of service, some   
OL,16,Fstaff could secure rates of up to      
OL,17,F#13.15 an hour. Retailers including    
OL,18,FTesco have made similar moves recently 
OL,19,Fas firms try to retain staff struggling
OL,20,Fwith high living costs.                
